{"title_page": "COVID-19 pandemic in the Comoros", "text_new": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in the Comoros}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = COVID-19 pandemic in the Comoros\n| map1 = File:Comoros covid-2020-05-02.png\n| legend1 = Islands with one or more cases\n| map2 = \n| legend2 = \n| map3 = \n| legend3 = \n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Comoros]]\n| first_case = [[Moroni, Comoros|Moroni]]\n| arrival_date = 23 April 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=4|day1=23|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| confirmed_cases = 3<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://stopcoronavirus.km|title=Stop Covid-19 Comores|language=fr|access-date=4 May 2020|website=Stop Coronavirus.km}}</ref> (2020-05-03)\n| recovery_cases  = 0\n| deaths          = 0\n| total_ili = \n| website = [https://stopcoronavirus.km stopcoronavirus.km]\n}}\nThe '''[[COVID-19 pandemic]] in Comoros''' is part of the ongoing global [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|viral pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), which was confirmed to have reached [[Comoros]] on 30 April 2020.<ref name=\"first\"/>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{Medical cases chart\n|numwidth=ttd\n|barwidth=thin\n\n|disease=COVID-19\n|location=the Comoros\n|outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n\n<!-- |togglesbar=\n<div class=\"nomobile\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|mar}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|apr}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|may}}\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15 mw-customtoggle-may-l15 mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15 mw-customtoggle-may-l15\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"border:2px solid lightblue; padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n</div>\n\n|collapsible=y --> <!-- remove comment when medical case becomes too big -->\n|data=\n<!--date;deaths;recoveries;total_cases;;;total_cases;+%;-->\n2020-04-30; 0;  0; 1\n2020-05-01; 0;  0; 1\n2020-05-02; 0;  0; 3\n2020-05-03; 0;  0; 3\n\n|caption=Source: [https://stopcoronavirus.km stopcoronavirus.km]\n}}\n===April===\nAs a preventative measure, arriving travellers were to be quarantined for 14 days upon arrival. In order to prevent the spread of the virus, the government has cancelled all incoming flights and banned large gatherings.<ref name=\"measures\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/comoros/coronavirus|title=Coronavirus - Comoros travel advice|website=GOV.UK|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 April 2020, a person arriving in [[Mayotte]] from the Comoros tested positive for COVID-19.<ref name=\"comoros_mayotte\">{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/un-cas-de-coronavirus-a-ete-importe-des-comores-823226.html|title=Un cas de Coronavirus a \u00e9t\u00e9 import\u00e9 des Comores|language=fr | access-date=15 April 2020| website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 April, [[Dominique Voynet]], Director of Mayotte Regional Health Agency, announced that a person who died on 8 April in [[Mayotte]] of COVID-19 was Said Toihir, the [[Grand Mufti]] of the Comoros.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/le-grand-mufti-des-comores-est-decede-du-coronavirus-823672.html|title=Le grand Mufti des Comores est d\u00e9c\u00e9d\u00e9 du Coronavirus|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> The announcement caused a diplomatic rift between Comoros and [[France]]. [[Mohamed El-Amine Souef]], Foreign Minister of Comoros said \"If a case is confirmed in the Comoros, it is not Dominique Voynet to announce it, we have been independent since 6 July 1975.\" <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/l-union-des-comores-denonce-une-violation-du-secret-medical-et-professionnel-823988.html|title=l'Union des Comores d\u00e9nonce \" Une violation du secret m\u00e9dical et professionnel \"|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 April, the [[World Health Organization]] delivered medical aid to the Comoros.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afro.who.int/fr/news/comores-loms-sur-tous-les-fronts-contre-le-covid-19|title=Comores : l\u2019OMS sur tous les fronts contre le Covid-19|language=fr|website=[[World Health Organization]]|access-date=30 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 April, the rapper Cheikh Mc released a video saying that his wife had been infected by COVID-19. The rapper was arrested by the gendarmerie at 16:00 after the video was shared many times.<ref name=\"cheikh_mc\">{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-le-rappeur-cheikh-mc-a-annonce-que-sa-femme-etait-atteinte-du-covid-19-824878.html |title=Coronavirus : Le rappeur Cheikh Mc a annonc\u00e9 que sa femme \u00e9tait atteinte du Covid 19 |website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref> Cheikh Mc had been released again around 21:00.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/cheikhmcofficiel/posts/3074454105927425|title=Je suis bien arriv\u00e9 \u00e0 la maison|website=Cheikh Mc Official via Facebook|access-date=30 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> The Ministry of Health announced on 21 April that Cheikh Mc's fears could not be confirmed without testing, but the contacts of his wife will be followed up.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://stopcoronavirus.km/actualit%C3%A9s/2020/04/21/communiqu%C3%A9-n-8-r%C3%A9action-face-aux-inqui%C3%A9tudes-des-derni%C3%A8res-24-heures/|title=Communiqu\u00e9 N\u00b09 : R\u00e9action face aux inqui\u00e9tudes des derni\u00e8res 24 heures|website=Stop Coronavirus.km|access-date=1 May 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 April, a [[polymerase chain reaction]] (PCR) screening machine was delivered and the Comoros can start testing for COVID-19 from 23 April onwards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://stopcoronavirus.km/actualit%C3%A9s/2020/04/23/les-comore-se-dotent-d%E2%80%99un-pcr/|title=Les Comores se dotent d\u2019un PCR|website=Stop Coronovirus.km|access-date=30 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n\nOn '''30 April''', the first case was confirmed, a 50-year-old man who was admitted to the El-Maarouf Hospital in [[Moroni, Comoros|Moroni]] on 23 April.<ref name=\"first\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.china.org.cn/world/Off_the_Wire/2020-04/30/content_75996788.htm|title=Comoros reports 1st COVID-19 case |website=China.org.cn|access-date=30 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"announchement\"/> The patient had been in contact with a Franco-Comorian national on 18 March. The patient is in a reasonable condition.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://stopcoronavirus.km/actualit%C3%A9s/2020/04/30/le-pr%C3%A9sident-azali-assoumani-annonce-un-premier-cas-de-covid-19-aux-comores/|title=Le Pr\u00e9sident Azali Assoumani annonce un premier cas de Covid-19 aux Comores|website=Stop Coronavirus.km|access-date=1 May 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n<br>President [[Azali Assoumani]] also disclosed that a [[curfew]] had been instituted.<ref name=\"announchement\">{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/le-president-azali-reconnait-l-existence-du-covid-19-aux-comores-828240.html|title=Le pr\u00e9sident Azali reconnait l\u2019existence du covid-19 aux Comores |language=fr|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|access-date=30 April 2020}}</ref>\n===May===\n\nOn 2 May 2020, it was announced that two more cases had tested positive. All cases are on the island of [[Grande Comore]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://stopcoronavirus.km/actualit%C3%A9s/2020/05/02/deux-nouveaux-cas-test%C3%A9s-positifs-au-covid-19/|title=Deux nouveaux cas test\u00e9s positifs au covid-19|access-date=2 May 2020|website=Stop Coronavirus.km|language=fr}}</ref>\n<br>\nThere was a video conference between President Assoumani and President [[Andry Rajoelina|Rajoelina]] of [[Madagascar]]. Madagascar will send medical aid to the Comoros.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://stopcoronavirus.km/actualit%C3%A9s/2020/05/02/entretien-entre-le-pr%C3%A9sident-malgache-et-le-pr%C3%A9sident-comorien-sur-le-covid-19/|title=Entretien entre le Pr\u00e9sident Malgache et le Pr\u00e9sident Comorien sur le Covid-19|access-date=3 May 2020|website=Stop Coronavirus.km|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n==Preventive measures==\n* All schools have been closed.<ref name=\"announchement\"/>\n* Arriving travellers are quarantined for 14 days.<ref name=\"measures\"/>\n* Incoming flights are banned.<ref name=\"measures\"/>\n* Large gatherings are banned.<ref name=\"measures\"/>\n* Curfew has been instituted between 20:00 to 05:00 as of 25 April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://stopcoronavirus.km/actualit%C3%A9s/2020/04/26/communiqu%C3%A9-10-couvre-feu/|title=Communiqu\u00e9 #10 : Couvre feu|website=Stop Coronavirus.km|access-date=1 May 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mayotte]]\n\n==External links==\n* [https://stopcoronavirus.km Official site]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in the Comoros]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Africa]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Comoros]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in th